# README for openssl


## PowerPC64 Big-Endian Notice

When building OpenSSL on **ppc64 (big-endian)** systems, the configuration option
`enable-ec_nistp_64_gcc_128` must **not be used**.

This optimization is designed for **little-endian architectures** and relies on
arithmetic assumptions that are not valid on big-endian platforms. OpenSSL
explicitly prevents its use and the build will fail with an error similar to:

    error: "Can not enable ec_nistp_64_gcc_128 on big-endian systems"

Since this project targets **ppc64 big-endian**, this option has been
intentionally removed from the build configuration.

This does **not affect normal cryptographic functionality or performance**.
OpenSSL still enables PowerPC-specific assembly implementations and runtime CPU
feature detection for algorithms such as AES, SHA, and GHASH when building with
the `linux-ppc64` target.
